Airflow has a side effect that will be difficult to fix, so I changed this test a bit.
The following message began to appear at the beginning of the output.
```
[2019-11-12 00:15:08,234] {cli_action_loggers.py:67} DEBUG - Calling callbacks: [<function default_action_log at 0x7f37bf1aed08>]
```

        self.assertIn("Task runme_0\n".format(DEFAULT_DATE.isoformat()), output)

        mock_run.assert_not_called()  # Dry run shouldn't run the backfill
